Q: What is Object oriented Programming?

A: The OOP a programming pattern in computer science that relies on the concept of classes and objects.
   It is used to structure a software program into simple, reusable pieces of code blueprints (usually called classes), which are used to create individual Objects / instances of the classes.

 Q: How does one Object calls/invokes another object in java?

 A:


-> A class is considered as a blueprint which will have STATE(variables) & BEHAVIOUR(Methods) which contains the data of object created from the class.

-> A New object will be created using CONSTRUCTOR (provide some code snippet)

-> OOPS concepts

1. Encapsulation
2. Abstraction
